    "This approach involved the construction of a hierarchical exercise graph, effectively capturing the dependencies in exercise learning [55].",
    "Song et al.",
    "introduced a Joint graph convolutional networkbased deep Knowledge Tracing (JKT) system that connects exercises across different concepts, grasps high-level semantic details, and enhances the model's interpretability [56].",
    "introduced a session graph-based knowledge tracing (SGKT) that captures dynamic graphs through student interactions during a session and mimics the student response process.",
    "Additionally, they utilized a gated graph neural network to discern the knowledge states of students [57]."
